00:05:20.937 --> 00:05:24.165
Measured or
synthetic room impulse responses can be

75
00:05:24.165 --> 00:05:29.400
used to recreate the acoustic
impression of the corresponding space.

76
00:05:29.400 --> 00:05:34.340
If we convolve a room impulse response of
a cathedral with the sound sample measured

77
00:05:34.340 --> 00:05:36.060
in a room without echo,

78
00:05:36.060 --> 00:05:41.070
the resulting signal will sound as
if it was recorded in the cathedral.

79
00:05:41.070 --> 00:05:43.890
This process is called auralization.

80
00:05:43.890 --> 00:05:44.600
It is used, for

81
00:05:44.600 --> 00:05:50.280
example, in virtual reality to create
realistically sounding virtual spaces.

82
00:05:50.280 --> 00:05:53.570
Another application example is,
of course, in music production.

83
00:05:55.370 --> 00:05:58.370
As you will hear,
even this simple convulation can

84
00:05:58.370 --> 00:06:03.510
evoke correct mental imagery about
the space we are auralizing.

